## Level-set random field parameterisation {.scrollable}
### Example in 2D. 

Unknown physical property $\kappa(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{cc} \kappa_1(x)&\textrm{if}~x\in \Omega_{A},\\
\kappa_2(x)&\textrm{if}~x\notin \Omega_{A}.\end{array}\right.$

$\Omega_{A}$: Unknown anomalous region = [shape optiisation].{alert]. 

- [**Level-set parameterisation**]{.fg style="--col: #e64173"}: 
  - Introduce an artificial level-set (LS) function $L(x)$.


::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="50%"}


- Anomalous: 
  - $\Omega_{A}=\{x\in \mathbb{R}^{2}\vert \,\,\red{L(x)}>\lambda\}$

 

$$
\kappa(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{cc} \red{\kappa_1(x)}&\textrm{if}~\red{L(x)}>\lambda,\\
\red{\kappa_2(x)}&\textrm{if}~\red{L(x)}\leq \lambda.\end{array}\right.
$$

$$\big(L, \kappa_1,\kappa_2\big)\mapsto \kappa$$
$$\mathcal{P}(L,\kappa_1,\kappa_2)=\kappa$$
:::

::: {.column width="50%"}

- Non-anomalous: 
  - $D\setminus A_{L}^{\lambda}.$


::: {layout-ncol=3}

![LS function ($L(x)$)](Figs/param1.png){height=8cm}

![Truncated LS](Figs/param2.png){height=8cm width=70%}

![Random field $\kappa(x)$](Figs/param3.png){height=8cm}

:::


:::

:::

[**Bayesian level-set inversion**]{.fg style="--col: #e64173"} [@Level]:

Instead of inferring $u(x)=\kappa(x)$, infer $u(x)=(L(x), \kappa_{1}(x),\kappa_{2}(x))$, i.e.

- Prior $\mathbb{P}(u)=\mathbb{P}(L)\mathbb{P}(\kappa_{1})\mathbb{P}(\kappa_{2})$

- Compute/approximate posterior: $\mathbb{P}(d^{\eta}\vert u)$

- Push forward posterior $\mathcal{P}_\#\mathbb{P}(d^{\eta}\vert u)$. 







## Gaussian Random Fields (GRFs) {.scrollable}

$L(x)\sim N(m, \mathcal{C})$

<details>
  <summary> Whittle-Matern GRF (see details). 
  </summary>

Autocorrelation function:
$$
ACF(x) = \sigma^2\frac{1}{2^{\nu-1}\Gamma(\nu)} \norm{\frac{x}{L}}^\nu K_\nu \Big(\norm{\frac{x}{L}}\Big).
$$
$\nu$ (smoothness); $L$ (intrinsic length-scale); $\sigma$ (amplitude scale).

</details>


::: { layout-ncol=1}

![**(a)** Continuous Matérn random fields.](Figs/matern_random_fields_fft.jpg){width=100%}

![**(b)** Thresholded Matérn random fields.](Figs/matern_thresholded_fft.jpg){width=100%}

:::


