::: {.columns }


::: {.column width="70%"}

::: callout-note

## Forward Problem
Given $\red{u(x)=(c(x),k(x),R_{I},R_{E})}$ find $\blue{T(x, t)}$: 
$$
\red{c(x)}\frac{\partial \blue{T(x, t)}}{\partial t} =\nabla \cdot \red{k(x)} \nabla \blue{T(x, t)}
$$
Convective BCs on the internal/external surfaces $\mathcal{S}_{\alpha},~(\alpha=I,E)$

$$
\begin{align*}
 - \red{k(x)} \nabla T(x, t)\cdot\mathbf{n}(x)=\red{R_{\alpha}^{-1}}[T(x,t)- \green{T_{\alpha}(t)}]
\end{align*}
$$



:::

::: callout-important

## Inverse Problem

Find $\red{u(x)=(c(x),k(x),R_{I},R_{E})}$ given $\blue{T(x,t)\big\vert_{\mathcal{S}_{\alpha}}}$ and  $\blue{Q_{\alpha}(x,t)\equiv -k(x)\nabla T(x,t)\big\vert_{\mathcal{S}_{\alpha}}}$.

